und in agony.Reaching him in three steps,Varx descends without mercy and his brains are scattered upon the four winds.I turn to a quivering Sana and pull her into my arms.&quot;There i told you no one would harm you,was i not right?&quot; <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fbe5b4><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/uxxsanainchainsxx.showPublicProfile?language=EN>XxSanaInChainsxX</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>registered user</span><br>  Posts: 27<br> <font color=#993300>(4/14/02 3:27:13 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm40.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=21.topic&index=82>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://hometown.aol.com/variaavande/images/sana.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: The next morning...</span><hr size=1> She couldn't speak. Fear had gripped her little heart once again, and she sobbed into Kally's warm embrace. &quot;I knew they would come for me...&quot; she spoke after some time. &quot;You saved me...&quot; Emotion overtook her and she lifted her head and kissed Kally's lips. When she realized what she had done she quickly turned her head, but didn't back away from the gentle hold Kally had on her. She refused to look at the bodies, for she did not want to appear like a savage... if she looked, she would surely tear their defenseless corpses limb from limb... and there was no need for that. She was safe... <p><html> <font face="vivaldi" size="+2" color="#87ceeb"> <center> Sana ~ Escaped Slave </font> </center> </html></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fed995><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/ukally2000uk.showPublicProfile?language=EN>kally2000uk</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>registered user</span><br>  Posts: 51<br> <font color=#993300>(4/14/02 2:12:20 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm40.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=21.topic&index=83>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://hometown.aol.com/variaavande/images/kally101.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: The next morning...</span><hr size=1> I embrace Sana once more,&quot;You have no need to fear little one,you are safe here,.&quot; i brush the hair from her face and wipe a tear from her cheek.I look at the trash whose souls i have just sent to Andraste,&quot;Come Sana,let us be away from here,a foul stench taints the place.&quot; <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fbe5b4><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/uxxsanainchainsxx.showPublicProfile?language=EN>XxSanaInChainsxX</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>registered user</span><br>  Posts: 28<br> <font color=#993300>(4/14/02 3:23:22 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm40.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=21.topic&index=84>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://hometown.aol.com/variaavande/images/sana.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: The next morning...</span><hr size=1> Sana nodded. &quot;Thank you again,&quot; she said, and took Kally's hand once more, waiting to be led to a nicer spot. She hoped they could maybe have a picnic lunch or something. <p><html> <font face="vivaldi" size="+2" color="#87ceeb"> <center> Sana ~ Escaped Slave </font> </center> </html></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fed995><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/ukally2000uk.showPublicProfile?language=EN>kally2000uk</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>registered user</span><br>  Posts: 52<br> <font color=#993300>(4/16/02 2:00:11 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm40.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=21.topic&index=85>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://hometown.aol.com/variaavande/images/kally101.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: The next morning...</span><hr size=1> After returning quickly to the village and getting some things,we return to the lake,the opposite end to the one where i had just slain the strangers.I pull a chicken out of the pouch i had fetched,pull off one of the legs and offer it to Sana.As she leans forward to bite into it,i remove it quickly and kiss her instead. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fbe5b4><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/uxxsanainchainsxx.showPublicProfile?language=EN>XxSanaInChainsxX</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>registered user</span><br>  Posts: 29<br> <font color=#993300>(4/17/02 12:22:27 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm40.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=21.topic&index=86>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://hometown.aol.com/variaavande/images/sana.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: The next morning...</span><hr size=1> Sana giggled and returned the kiss briefly before sitting up straight. She glanced around nervously to make sure no one had seen. Then she smiled and blushed a little bit, and reached for the chicken leg. She was hungry. She looked lovingly at Kally, her rescuer, her friend, as she ate the chicken. &quot;Mmm, this is gooood,&quot; she said and took another bite. &quot;Thank you for doing this. I've always wanted to have a picnic by a lake...&quot; <p><html> <font face="vivaldi" size="+2" color="#87ceeb"> <center> Sana ~ Escaped Slave </font> </center> </html></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fed995><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/ukally2000uk.showPublicProfile?language=EN>kally2000uk</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>registered user</span><br>  Posts: 53<br> <font color=#993300>(4/17/02 1:00:14 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm40.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=21.topic&index=87>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://hometown.aol.com/variaavande/images/kally101.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: The next morning...</span><hr size=1> &quot;You are welcome Sana.&quot; i reply with a smile,guessing to myself that it was a long time since she had enjoyed such tranquility.I could only guess at the horrors which haunted her mind.Perhaps with time the bad memories would fade.I lean forward and stroke the side of her face which prompts an enquiring smile.&quot;You smile beautifully Sana,it pleases me to see you doing it more.&quot; <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fbe5b4><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/uxxsanainchainsxx.showPublicProfile?language=EN>XxSanaInChainsxX</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>registered user</span><br>  Posts: 30<br> <font color=#993300>(4/17/02 2:14:15 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm40.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=21.topic&index=88>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://hometown.aol.com/variaavande/images/sana.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: The next morning...</span><hr size=1> She smiled again and giggled. Then turned serious once more. &quot;I finally have a reason to smile...&quot; <p><html> <font face="vivaldi" size="+2" color="#87ceeb"> <center> Sana ~ Escaped Slave </font> </center> </html></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top">  Page <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm40.showMessageRange?topicID=21.topic&start=1&stop=20>1</a><a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm40.showMessageRange?topicID=21.topic&start=21&stop=40>2</a><a href=http://pub11